 # Spec [[cat001]] [[cat003]] [[board]]
@@ -14,6 +14,154 @@ The platform-engineer [[pn002]] needs to rotate service credentials without
 downtime. Story [[us003]] asks for live rotation with a 5-minute overlap and
 zero 5xx during the rotation window.
 
+## solution
+Lean on the existing [[ft002|vault-secrets]] feature: every service already
+reads credentials at runtime via `secret(name)`. Extend the vault client with
+a short-lived in-process cache that re-reads on a configurable TTL (default
+60s) and accepts dual-valued secrets so the old value stays acceptable for a
+5-minute overlap window. Rotation is performed by a small CLI
+(`rotate-secret`) that writes both `<name>` (new) and `<name>.prev` (old) to
+Vault, waits for cache TTL × 2 propagation, then clears `<name>.prev`. No
+service restart required.
+
+ADRs the plan leans on:
+- [[adr0001]] — basic-auth stays as the authentication mechanism; rotation
+  applies to all secret types but does not change the auth shape.
+
+Features consumed:
+- [[ft002|vault-secrets]] — extended (additive: TTL cache + dual-value
+  read) without breaking the existing `secret(name)` API.
+
+## plan
+
+### File tree
+
+```
+src/lib/vault.py                    ← extend with TTL cache + dual-value read
+src/lib/rotate_secret.py            ← new CLI entry point
+src/services/auth/main.py           ← no code change; verify cache picks up
+src/services/metrics/main.py        ← no code change; verify cache picks up
+src/services/reports/main.py        ← no code change; verify cache picks up
+tests/lib/test_vault.py             ← cache + dual-value unit tests
+tests/integration/test_rotation.py  ← end-to-end rotation, synthetic 5xx
+```
+
+### Conventions
+
+- Vault keys remain flat strings; dual-value uses suffix `.prev` convention.
+- Cache TTL defaults read from env `VAULT_CACHE_TTL` (seconds, default 60).
+- All new code lives under `src/lib/` to keep the feature reusable across
+  services (consistent with [[ft002]] component boundary).
+- CLI is a single-file script using `argparse`; no new framework.
+
+### Anti-patterns to avoid
+
+- Do not introduce a new Feature zettel for the cache — it is an additive
+  extension of [[ft002]] within its existing api_surface.
+- Do not require service restarts; the whole point is no downtime.
+- Do not push out cache TTL > 5 minutes — would defeat the overlap window.
+
+### Known limitations
+
+- Initial implementation polls Vault on TTL expiry; a push-based invalidation
+  is out of scope for this spec.
+- The rotation CLI runs interactively; full automation lives in a follow-up.
+
+## tasks
+
+### Task 1: Extend vault client with TTL cache and dual-value read
+
+#### type
+feature
+
+#### effort
+4h
+
+#### depends
+- none
+
+#### files_touched
+- src/lib/vault.py
+- tests/lib/test_vault.py
+
+#### success_criteria
+- `secret(name)` returns cached value within TTL window
+- After TTL expiry, next call refreshes from Vault
+- When both `<name>` and `<name>.prev` are present, `secret(name)` returns
+  the current value but `secret_accepts(name, value)` returns True for either
+- Existing callers see no behavior change when no `.prev` key exists
+
+#### edge_cases
+- Vault unreachable during refresh → return stale cached value, log warning
+- Cache TTL = 0 → behave as today (always read through)
+- `.prev` written without `<name>` → treat as missing (do not promote)
+
+#### test_plan
+- Unit: TTL boundary (read at t=59s cached, t=61s refreshed)
+- Unit: dual-value `secret_accepts` returns True for old + new
+- Unit: Vault error returns cached value + emits warning log
+
+### Task 2: Implement `rotate-secret` CLI
+
+#### type
+feature
+
+#### effort
+3h
+
+#### depends
+- Task 1
+
+#### files_touched
+- src/lib/rotate_secret.py
+
+#### success_criteria
+- `rotate-secret <name> <new-value>` writes new value to `<name>` and moves
+  prior value to `<name>.prev`
+- After `2 × VAULT_CACHE_TTL` it clears `<name>.prev`
+- Exit code non-zero on Vault write failure with reason printed to stderr
+
+#### edge_cases
+- Pre-existing `<name>.prev` → overwrite and warn (caller may have aborted
+  a prior rotation)
+- Vault write of new value succeeds but `.prev` write fails → roll back the
+  new value to keep state consistent
+
+#### test_plan
+- Integration: rotation against a vault test double, assert key state at
+  each stage (pre, mid, post)
+- Integration: simulate failed `.prev` write, assert rollback
+
+### Task 3: End-to-end rotation under load
+
+#### type
+task
+
+#### effort
+3h
+
+#### depends
+- Task 1
+- Task 2
+
+#### files_touched
+- tests/integration/test_rotation.py
+
+#### success_criteria
+- Synthetic check fires 10 req/s at all three services while rotation runs
+- Zero 5xx during the rotation window
+- Old credential stays valid for ≥ 5 minutes after rotation
+
+#### edge_cases
+- Service mid-request when secret changes → request completes with the
+  resolved-at-entry credential
+- Two rotations in quick succession (< TTL window) → second rotation waits
+  or errors cleanly, never strands a `.prev` of a `.prev`
+
+#### test_plan
+- Integration: synthetic load + rotation, assert request log has no 5xx
+- Integration: time-warp the cache TTL, assert overlap window is honoured
+
